<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Sparkling Juices Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Health Concerns:</strong>            Consumers are increasingly becoming health-conscious, leading to concerns over added sugars and artificial ingredients in sparkling juices. This trend pressures manufacturers to reformulate products with natural sweeteners or to reduce sugar content, which can impact flavor and customer satisfaction.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Intense Competition:</strong>            The market is crowded with established beverage brands and new entrants, resulting in fierce competition. Differentiation becomes challenging as brands struggle to convey unique selling propositions amidst a vast array of options.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Supply Chain Disruptions:</strong>            Fluctuations in the availability of ingredients due to global supply chain disruptions can hinder production efficiency. This unpredictability can lead to raw material shortages or increased costs, affecting overall profitability.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Changing Consumer Preferences:</strong>            Rapid shifts in consumer preferences pose a challenge for brands that fail to adapt product lines quickly. As consumers gravitate toward beverages perceived as healthier or more functional, companies must innovate continuously to meet these evolving demands.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong>            The beverage industry is subject to stringent regulations regarding labeling, food safety, and health claims. Staying compliant requires ongoing adaptations to formulations and marketing strategies, which can be both resource-intensive and costly.        </li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Sparkling Juices Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Product Innovation:</strong>            Thereâ€™s a growing demand for unique flavors and 